[SN]TITLE[SN]
Gloucestershire v Nottinghamshire: Gareth Roderick builds hosts' recovery v Notts

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Gloucestershire recovered from 77-4 to close on 256-7 on day one thanks to Gareth Roderick's unbeaten 88 against Division Two visitors Nottinghamshire.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
After electing to bowl, leaders Notts were on top when Cameron Bancroft and Graeme van Buuren both fell to Brett Hutton in consecutive balls.
Roderick and captain Phil Mustard's 83-run fifth-wicket stand ended as Mustard was caught off Harry Gurney (3-56).
After Kieran Noema-Barnett's 35, Craig Miles (14*) will resume with Roderick.
